properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 2 at 8:15AM PST until February 2 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Dense Fog in Sacramento Area this Morning and Gusty Northerly
Winds across the Valley Today...

.Areas of dense fog have formed in the Sacramento metro area,
creating travel impacts from low visibilities. A strong upper
trough moving through today will bring a period of gusty
northerly winds. Expected wind gusts are likely to reach 30 to 45
mph at times from the late morning through the evening. Breezy
conditions to continue into Monday as the system exits toward the
southwestern U.S.

* WHAT...Northerly winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts around 30 to 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Sacramento Valley, Carquinez Strait and Delta,
Northern San Joaquin Valley and Northeast Foothills/Sacramento
Valley Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 7 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Expect difficult driving conditions at times.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST THIS EVENING
